'''Eva Russo''' (born 20 December 1966)<ref name="dizionario">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=J5OpwwKggrsC&pg=PA689&lpg=PA689&dq=vilma+seghetti&source=bl&ots=p84xnMEtZZ&sig=jkXeHF5-lGG-j_9sx1Vwbn60hiQ&hl=en#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=Dizionario Del Calcio Italiano|publisher=Baldini&Castoldi|accessdate=2012-08-31|first=Marco|last=Sappino|language=Italian|isbn=978-8880898627|page=686|year=2000}}</ref> is an [[Italy|Italian]] [[Actor|actress]] and former international [[women's soccer|football]] [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]].
Russo had 57 caps for the [[Italy women's national football team]] in December 1989 when she failed a drugs test ahead of a match with [[Switzerland women's national football team|Switzerland]] and received a six-month suspension.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/1990/02/16/lo-spinello-in-ritiro-sospesa-la-numero.html|title=Lo Spinello In Ritiro Sospesa La Numero Uno |publisher=[[la Repubblica]]|accessdate=2012-09-01|first=Eugenio|last=Capodacqua|language=Italian|date=1990-02-17}}</ref>
While playing for [[S.S. Lazio Calcio Femminile|Lazio]], she was engaged to the male Lazio footballer [[Francesco Dell'Anno]]. The engagement broke off after four years. Russo also worked as an actress.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/1990/02/17/storia-di-eva-con-mistero.html|title=Storia Di Eva Con Mistero|publisher=[[la Repubblica]]|accessdate=2012-09-01|first=Fulvio|last=Bianchi|language=Italian|date=1990-02-16}}</ref>
