'''Gladson Dungdung''' (born 2 May 1980) is a human rights [[Human rights activists|activist]] and writer based in [[Ranchi]], India. He was one of the first [[authors]] published by [[Adivaani]] with the English language book "Whose Country is it Anyway?", launched in 2013 at the [[New Delhi World Book Fair]].<ref name="publisher">{{cite news |title=Voice of the santhals |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-12-31/kolkata/45739002_1_adivasi-tribal-children-santhali |publisher=The Times of India|date=31 December 2013}}</ref><ref name="voice">{{cite news |title=A new voice |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/a-new-voice/article5076553.ece|publisher=The Hindu|date=31 August 2013}}</ref><ref name="interview">{{cite AV media | date=6 February 2013 |title=Writer and the Politics: Gladson Dungdung |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ty4wSQHJNYo| medium=video | publisher=Tehelka TV}}</ref>
He has spoken internationally on human rights issues, including [[police atrocities]] and [[gross violation of the rights of indigenous peoples]]. <ref name="Australian">{{cite news |title=India rocked again by rape case|url=http://www.theaustralian.com.au/news/world/india-rocked-again-by-rape-case/story-e6frg6so-1226808940289#|publisher=The Australian|date=24 January 2014}}</ref><ref name="passport">{{cite news |title=Human rights activist's passport seized |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2014-01-21/ranchi/46409989_1_passport-office-police-verification-passport-act|publisher=The Times of India|date=21 January 2014}}</ref>
His passport was taken in January 2014, following "a sensitive report from state police" related to his travel to Germany and Thailand to speak about the gross human rights violation. He reported refusing to pay [[bribes]] during his passport application process.<ref name="passport"/><ref name="bribes">{{cite news |title=Jharkhand human rights activist Gladson Dungdung alleges harassment |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/jharkhand-human-rights-activist-gladson-dungdung-alleges-harassment/article5578877.ece|publisher=The Hindu|date=15 January 2014}}</ref>
