'''James Cavendish''' (circa 1749 – January 1808) was an [[Anglo-Irish]] politician.

Cavendish sat in the [[Irish House of Commons]] as the [[Member of Parliament]] for [[Lifford (Parliament of Ireland constituency)|Lifford]] between 1773 and 1776, before sitting for [[Banagher (Parliament of Ireland constituency)|Banagher]] from 1776 to 1783.<ref>E. M. Johnston-Liik, [https://books.google.co.uk/books/about/MPs_in_Dublin.html?id=jitdluWSybIC ''MPs in Dublin: Companion to History of the Irish Parliament, 1692-1800''] (Ulster Historical Foundation, 2006), p.77 (Retrieved 29 February 2016).</ref>

