'''Magomed Gadaborshev''' ({{lang-ru|Магомед Гадаборшев}}) (?&nbsp;– July 9, 2009) was a [[Russia]]n-[[Ingushetia]]n [[colonel]] who headed [[Ingushetia]]'s [[Forensics]] and Investigations Center.<ref name=rfe> {{cite news |first=|last=|title=Senior Ingushetia Official Dies After Attack |url=http://www.rferl.org/content/Senior_Ingushetia_Official_Dies_After_Attack/1773965.html|work=[[Radio Free Europe]]|publisher=|date=2009-07-10 |accessdate=2009-07-10}}</ref>
On July 7, 2009, attackers opened fire on Gadaborshev's car as he drove through the [[city center]] of [[Nazran]], the largest city in Ingushetia.<ref name=rfe/> He suffered gunshot wounds in the attack and fell into a [[coma]].<ref name=rfe/> Doctors pronounced Gadaborshev dead on July 9, 2009.<ref name=rfe/>
Gadaborshev's killing followed a string of attacks on and assassinations of Ingush officials in the preceding weeks.<ref name=rfe/> The [[President of Ingushetia]], [[Yunus-Bek Yevkurov]], was seriously wounded in a bombing on June 22, 2009.<ref name=rfe/> The deputy chief justice of the Supreme Court of Ingushetia [[Aza Gazgireeva]] and former deputy prime minister [[Bashir Aushev]] were also assassinated in separate shootings in June 2009.<ref name=nyt> {{cite news |first=|last=|title=Another Killing in Region Bordering Chechnya |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2009/06/14/world/europe/14ingushetia.html?_r=1&ref=world|work=[[Associated Press]]|publisher=[[New York Times]]|date=2009-06-10 |accessdate=2009-06-22}}</ref>
